  "prompt": "\"I didn't received the item yet\": is this grammatically correct?",
  "response": "The sentence **\"I didn't received the item yet\"** is **not grammatically correct**. Here's why:\n\n1. The auxiliary verb **\"did\"** (used in negative and question forms of the past simple tense) requires the base form of the main verb. The correct form for the main verb **\"receive\"** is **\"receive\"**, not **\"received\"**.\n   \n2. The word **\"yet\"** is correctly used to indicate that the action has not happened up to the present moment.\n\nThe corrected sentence is:  \n**\"I didn't receive the item yet.\"**  \n\nAlternatively, you could also say:  \n**\"I haven't received the item yet.\"**  \nThis version uses the present perfect tense, which is often more natural when referring to something expected but not yet completed.",
